New Records: David Wiese became the first Namibia player to win a Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup match with a Player of the Match performance
Key Match Events: The match went into a Super Over after a low-scoring duel, with Oman being dismissed for 109 in the regular innings
David Wiese and Gerhard Erasmus scored 21 runs in the Super Over by hitting four boundaries
Oman's Mehran Khan took three wickets and conceded only 10 runs in the Super Over
Pre-Game Insights: The match was a low-scoring encounter with Oman being dismissed for 109 runs in the 20th over
Post-Match Reflections: David Wiese expressed the emotional toll of the win and acknowledged the challenging pitch conditions
Namibia's performance in the Super Over showcased their composure under pressure
Miscellaneous Highlights: The match marked the first Super Over in a men's T20 World Cup since 2012
